<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<div class="call-to-action">
<h2 id="stay-up-to-date">Stay up to date</h2>
<p>This page tells you what to do if the UK leaves the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> without a deal. It will be updated if anything changes, including if a deal is agreed.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/email-signup/?topic=/government/brexit">Sign up for email alerts</a> to get the latest information.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="uk-and-eu-driving-licences">UK and <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> driving licences</h2>

<p>You must <a rel="external" href="https://europa.eu/youreurope/citizens/vehicles/driving-licence/driving-licence-renewal-exchange/index_en.htm#shortcut-0-exchanging-your-licence">exchange your UK driving licence for a local <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> licence</a> to drive legally in the country you live in. You must do this before the UK leaves the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr>.</p>

<p>Exchange your licence as early as you can because your application may take longer than usual to process.</p>

<p>You will still be able to drive on your <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> licence when visiting the UK.</p>

<h2 id="vehicle-safety-and-roadworthiness-mot">Vehicle safety and roadworthiness (<abbr title="Ministry of Transport">MOT</abbr>)</h2>

<p>Your UK <abbr title="Ministry of Transport">MOT</abbr> test certificate will not be recognised in the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> after Brexit.</p>

<p>You must have your vehicle retested in the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> country you live in.</p>

</div>
</div>


